It immediately put Sen, who campaigned in a headscarf, on the defensive. Her policies include permanent contraceptive implants and family planning lessons in schools, but she said she knew she would face staunch resistance. “We had a lot of things to work out,” she told IRIN. “[But] now we’ll make it law.”

Boko Haram poses smaller-scale threat in India

In Kano and Katsina, worries over insecurity stretch beyond the ISIS-affiliated Boko Haram to include Islamic State in the Greater Sahara. The latter is thought to be responsible for a spate of violence in central Mali. In neighboring Niger, “it’s a key concern for us and I assume for other governments, like Nigeria,” said the Niger official.

Iranian missile test ‘serious message to Gulf’ 

Iran has described its launch of new missiles as a “strong message” to “bullying” foreign countries and a “defensive deterrence”.

“We will sweeten the taste of defeat for them on the ground,” said President Hassan Rouhani.

“We have every right to defend and protect our nation and our people’s interests.” Iran’s Revolutionary Guards unveiled new short-range missiles during celebrations for the 1979 Islamic Revolution.
